1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Objects resist changes in motion — that's why seatbelts matter.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:10,400
This resistance is known as inertia, the tendency of objects to keep doing what they're doing.

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:16,400
When you're in a car and it suddenly stops, your body wants to keep moving.

4
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,400
That's why seatbelts save lives.

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:22,800
Inertia is everywhere — from riding a bike to playing sports.

6
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,400
Don't underestimate its power!

7
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:29,600
Understanding inertia helps you make safe choices every day, especially on the road.

8
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,000
Want to learn more surprising science?

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,600
Hit that follow button!
